# Clerk Migration - Environment Variables Template

## Client-Side (.env or .env.local)
# These variables are safe to expose to the browser

# Clerk Publishable Key (pk_test_xxx for development, pk_live_xxx for production)
VITE_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_your_key_here

# Supabase URL
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co

# Supabase Anon Key (public key, protected by RLS)
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJxxx_your_anon_key_here

## Server-Side (For Supabase Edge Functions or API routes)
# ⚠️ NEVER expose these variables to the client

# Clerk Secret Key (for server-side verification)
CLERK_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_your_secret_key_here

# Clerk Webhook Secret (for verifying webhook signatures)
CLERK_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_your_webhook_secret_here

# Supabase Service Role Key (bypasses RLS - NEVER expose to client)
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=eyJxxx_your_service_role_key_here

## Notes:
# 1. Get Clerk keys from: https://dashboard.clerk.com → Your App → API Keys
# 2. Get Supabase keys from: https://app.supabase.com → Your Project → Settings → API
# 3. Webhook secret is generated when you create a webhook in Clerk Dashboard
# 4. For production, use environment variables in your deployment platform (Vercel, Netlify, etc.)
# 5. NEVER commit this file with real keys to git (add .env.local to .gitignore)
